704580f-a.title: Brooklyn: Fulton Street - Georgia Avenue
704580f-a.text:
(1)
Fulton Street, at the N.W. corner of Georgia Ave., showing M. and
A. Bookman's drygooda,, clothing and shoe store which was established at
this location in 1852. I 1874 it moved to Jamaica and Georgi Aves.
It was no longer in business in 1908.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, showing also the Fulton Street Elevated lines of the
P.M.T.
April 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(3)
The sase, another view east on Fulton Street.
April 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

704615f-a.title: Brooklyn: Georgia Avenue - Fulton Street
704615f-a.text:
Georgia Ave., east side, south of Fulton Street. In the background is
the Long 1sland R.R. structure. In the left foreground (No. 33) is the
Wartburg Chapel (Lutheran).
April 1929.
